{
  "id": 6317308531965952,
  "name": "Mirroring of RTL MathML operators",
  "summary": "Support for character-level and glyph-level mirroring when rendering MathML operators in right-to-left mode.\r\n\r\nWhen using RTL mode some operators can be mirrored by changing them to another code point (e.g. a right parentheses becomes a left parentheses). This is character-level mirroring, with equivalences defined by Unicode's `Bidi_Mirrored` property. \r\n\r\nThere are operators that have no appropriate mirroring character. Glyph-level mirroring applies in this case, with the `rtlm` font feature, where another glyph can replace it in a mirrored context. Some existing implementations mirror the original glyph directly, but this may change the meaning for asymmetrical characters, such as the clockwise contour integral.",
  "markdown_fields": [],
